WorldStage Newsonline– – With a brand value of 3.3 billion dollars, the MTN Group  has been named the most valuable African brand in the Brand Finance Africa 150 ranking in 2020. Brand value is the net economic benefit that a brand owner would achieve by licencing the brand in the open marker. Its Group Executive, Corporate Affairs, Nompilo Morafo said in the survey by Brand Finance, it said, “Over the last year, Africa’s largest mobile operator has celebrated solid profits and impressive subscriber growth.” Morafo said the survey assessed the impact of COVID-19 on the enterprise value of all brands compared to their values on Jan. 1. It categorised the telecommunications sector as ‘limited impact’, which it said meant “minimal brand value loss or potential brand value growth”. This was due to the increasingly important role that mobile operators had played in keeping people connected in the time of the pandemic. He, however, said in July, Brand Finance also named MTN Group the most valuable South African brand. Morafo said a result of the group’s focussed was on improving the customer’s experience for subscribers. The company’s group executive said it was uniting 19, 000 employees around a shared belief, saying that everyone deserved the benefits of a modern connected life.